doc.after: After the arrival of European settlers in New South Wales some Indigenous Australians became translators and go betweens the best known was Bennelong who eventually adopted European dress and customs and travelled to England where he was presented to King George III Others such as Pemulwuy Yagan and Windradyne became famous for armed resistance to the European settlers
